      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There isn't much to complain about here aesthetically but there are a few elements of the gameplay that could've used some polishing. The overabundance of crafting in games is one of my pet peeves with modern gaming and when a key mechanic is foraging for elf-like helpers, being asked to do additional, less important foraging feels like such a chore. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The mechanic of throwing Spritelings also feels archaic. The lack of a lock-on feature feels like a strange oversight and the game suffers for it, especially since it's so integral to your progress. It feels like a choice from 2001 and not 2021.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Thankfully, even these flaws don't detract too much from what is otherwise a fantastic game.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
